-- Ikea to Invest $330 Million in Five Serbian Stores, NIN Reports
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-03-21T15:35:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/ikea-to-invest-330-million-in-five-serbian-stores-nin-reports.html
Ikea Group, the world’s largest
furniture retailer, will invest 250 million euros ($330 million)
in five stores it plans to open in  Serbia ,  NIN  newspaper
reported, citing the chief executive officer.  Construction of the first store may begin later this year
in the capital Belgrade and the rest will be in Serbia’s other
main cities, each employing about 400, the report quoted Mikael Ohlsson as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  